{
  "video_id": "CVa_IZVzUoc",
  "title": "Design at the Intersection of Technology and Biology | Neri Oxman | TED Talks",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 13037.0,
      "end_time": 15708.0,
      "text": "Two twin domes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 15708.0,
      "end_time": 19709.0,
      "text": "two radically opposed design cultures."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 19709.0,
      "end_time": 22773.0,
      "text": "One is made of thousands of steel parts,"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 22773.0,
      "end_time": 26035.0,
      "text": "the other of a single silk thread."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 26035.0,
      "end_time": 28936.0,
      "text": "One is synthetic, the other organic."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 28936.0,
      "end_time": 31237.0,
      "text": "One is imposed on the environment,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 31237.0,
      "end_time": 33666.0,
      "text": "the other creates it."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 33666.0,
      "end_time": 38032.0,
      "text": "One is designed for nature, the other is designed by her."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 38032.0,
      "end_time": 40949.0,
      "text": "Michelangelo said that when he looked at raw marble,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 40949.0,
      "end_time": 43425.0,
      "text": "he saw a figure struggling to be free."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 43425.0,
      "end_time": 49261.0,
      "text": "The chisel was Michelangelo&#39;s only tool."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 49261.0,
      "end_time": 51999.0,
      "text": "But living things are not chiseled."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 51999.0,
      "end_time": 53999.0,
      "text": "They grow."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 53999.0,
      "end_time": 59489.0,
      "text": "And in our smallest units of life, our cells, we carry all the information"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 59489.0,
      "end_time": 66155.0,
      "text": "that&#39;s required for every other cell to function and to replicate."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 66155.0,
      "end_time": 68922.0,
      "text": "Tools also have consequences."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 68922.0,
      "end_time": 73556.0,
      "text": "At least since the Industrial Revolution, the world of design has been dominated"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 73556.0,
      "end_time": 76703.0,
      "text": "by the rigors of manufacturing and mass production."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 76703.0,
      "end_time": 79999.0,
      "text": "Assembly lines have dictated a world made of parts,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 79999.0,
      "end_time": 82615.0,
      "text": "framing the imagination of designers and architects"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 82615.0,
      "end_time": 85743.0,
      "text": "who have been trained to think about their objects as assemblies"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 85743.0,
      "end_time": 90165.0,
      "text": "of discrete parts with distinct functions."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 90165.0,
      "end_time": 95434.0,
      "text": "But you don&#39;t find homogenous material assemblies in nature."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 95434.0,
      "end_time": 98054.0,
      "text": "Take human skin, for example."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 98054.0,
      "end_time": 101999.0,
      "text": "Our facial skins are thin with large pores."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 101999.0,
      "end_time": 105559.0,
      "text": "Our back skins are thicker, with small pores."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 105559.0,
      "end_time": 108201.0,
      "text": "One acts mainly as filter,"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 108201.0,
      "end_time": 109989.0,
      "text": "the other mainly as barrier,"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 109989.0,
      "end_time": 114281.0,
      "text": "and yet it&#39;s the same skin: no parts, no assemblies."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 114281.0,
      "end_time": 117670.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a system that gradually varies its functionality"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 117670.0,
      "end_time": 119835.0,
      "text": "by varying elasticity."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 119835.0,
      "end_time": 123801.0,
      "text": "So here this is a split screen to represent my split world view,"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 123801.0,
      "end_time": 128229.0,
      "text": "the split personality of every designer and architect operating today"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 128229.00000000001,
      "end_time": 130572.00000000001,
      "text": "between the chisel and the gene,"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 130572.0,
      "end_time": 135434.0,
      "text": "between machine and organism, between assembly and growth,"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 135434.0,
      "end_time": 138734.0,
      "text": "between Henry Ford and Charles Darwin."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 138734.0,
      "end_time": 141760.0,
      "text": "These two worldviews, my left brain and right brain,"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 141760.0,
      "end_time": 149754.0,
      "text": "analysis and synthesis, will play out on the two screens behind me."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 149754.0,
      "end_time": 152224.0,
      "text": "My work, at its simplest level,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 152224.0,
      "end_time": 154983.0,
      "text": "is about uniting these two worldviews,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 154983.0,
      "end_time": 157221.0,
      "text": "moving away from assembly"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 157221.0,
      "end_time": 161099.0,
      "text": "and closer into growth."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 161099.0,
      "end_time": 163235.0,
      "text": "You&#39;re probably asking yourselves:"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 163235.0,
      "end_time": 164766.0,
      "text": "Why now?"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 164766.0,
      "end_time": 170451.0,
      "text": "Why was this not possible 10 or even five years ago?"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 170451.0,
      "end_time": 172603.0,
      "text": "We live in a very special time in history,"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 172603.0,
      "end_time": 174699.0,
      "text": "a rare time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 174699.0,
      "end_time": 179302.0,
      "text": "a time when the confluence of four fields is giving designers access to tools"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 179302.0,
      "end_time": 182205.0,
      "text": "we&#39;ve never had access to before."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 182205.0,
      "end_time": 185093.0,
      "text": "These fields are computational design,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 185093.0,
      "end_time": 190125.0,
      "text": "allowing us to design complex forms with simple code;"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 190125.0,
      "end_time": 194183.0,
      "text": "additive manufacturing, letting us produce parts"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 194183.0,
      "end_time": 197833.0,
      "text": "by adding material rather than carving it out;"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 197833.0,
      "end_time": 201301.0,
      "text": "materials engineering, which lets us design the behavior of materials"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 201301.0,
      "end_time": 203042.0,
      "text": "in high resolution;"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 203042.0,
      "end_time": 204923.0,
      "text": "and synthetic biology,"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 204923.0,
      "end_time": 209491.0,
      "text": "enabling us to design new biological functionality by editing DNA."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 209491.0,
      "end_time": 211755.0,
      "text": "And at the intersection of these four fields,"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 211755.0,
      "end_time": 213492.0,
      "text": "my team and I create."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 213492.0,
      "end_time": 215921.0,
      "text": "Please meet the minds and hands"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 215921.0,
      "end_time": 219772.0,
      "text": "of my students."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 219772.0,
      "end_time": 225457.0,
      "text": "We design objects and products and structures and tools across scales,"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 225457.0,
      "end_time": 227252.0,
      "text": "from the large-scale,"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 227252.0,
      "end_time": 230792.0,
      "text": "like this robotic arm with an 80-foot diameter reach"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 230792.0,
      "end_time": 234950.0,
      "text": "with a vehicular base that will one day soon print entire buildings,"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 234950.0,
      "end_time": 239061.0,
      "text": "to nanoscale graphics made entirely of genetically engineered microorganisms"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 239061.0,
      "end_time": 241261.0,
      "text": "that glow in the dark."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 241261.0,
      "end_time": 243469.0,
      "text": "Here we&#39;ve reimagined the mashrabiya,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 243469.0,
      "end_time": 246866.0,
      "text": "an archetype of ancient Arabic architecture,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 246866.0,
      "end_time": 250454.0,
      "text": "and created a screen where every aperture is uniquely sized"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 250454.0,
      "end_time": 254999.0,
      "text": "to shape the form of light and heat moving through it."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 254999.0,
      "end_time": 256739.0,
      "text": "In our next project,"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 256738.99999999997,
      "end_time": 259972.99999999997,
      "text": "we explore the possibility of creating a cape and skirt --"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 259973.0,
      "end_time": 263187.0,
      "text": "this was for a Paris fashion show with Iris van Herpen --"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 263187.0,
      "end_time": 265999.0,
      "text": "like a second skin that are made of a single part,"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 265999.0,
      "end_time": 269589.0,
      "text": "stiff at the contours, flexible around the waist."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 269589.0,
      "end_time": 273813.0,
      "text": "Together with my long-term 3D printing collaborator Stratasys,"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 273813.0,
      "end_time": 278844.0,
      "text": "we 3D-printed this cape and skirt with no seams between the cells,"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 278844.0,
      "end_time": 281452.0,
      "text": "and I&#39;ll show more objects like it."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 281452.0,
      "end_time": 284889.0,
      "text": "This helmet combines stiff and soft materials"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 284889.0,
      "end_time": 288025.0,
      "text": "in 20-micron resolution."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 288025.0,
      "end_time": 290437.0,
      "text": "This is the resolution of a human hair."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 290437.0,
      "end_time": 293531.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s also the resolution of a CT scanner."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 293531.0,
      "end_time": 295096.0,
      "text": "That designers have access"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 295096.0,
      "end_time": 299518.0,
      "text": "to such high-resolution analytic and synthetic tools,"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 299518.0,
      "end_time": 304104.0,
      "text": "enables to design products that fit not only the shape of our bodies,"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 304104.0,
      "end_time": 308445.0,
      "text": "but also the physiological makeup of our tissues."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 308445.0,
      "end_time": 310477.0,
      "text": "Next, we designed an acoustic chair,"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 310477.0,
      "end_time": 313713.0,
      "text": "a chair that would be at once structural, comfortable"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 313713.0,
      "end_time": 316529.0,
      "text": "and would also absorb sound."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 316529.0,
      "end_time": 320999.0,
      "text": "Professor Carter, my collaborator, and I turned to nature for inspiration,"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 320999.0,
      "end_time": 323708.0,
      "text": "and by designing this irregular surface pattern,"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 323708.0,
      "end_time": 326659.0,
      "text": "it becomes sound-absorbent."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 326659.0,
      "end_time": 330583.0,
      "text": "We printed its surface out of 44 different properties,"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 330583.0,
      "end_time": 334000.0,
      "text": "varying in rigidity, opacity and color,"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 334000.0,
      "end_time": 338023.0,
      "text": "corresponding to pressure points on the human body."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 338023.0,
      "end_time": 342039.0,
      "text": "Its surface, as in nature, varies its functionality"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 342039.0,
      "end_time": 345690.0,
      "text": "not by adding another material or another assembly,"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 345690.0,
      "end_time": 352496.0,
      "text": "but by continuously and delicately varying material property."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 352496.0,
      "end_time": 356146.0,
      "text": "But is nature ideal?"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 356146.0,
      "end_time": 361185.0,
      "text": "Are there no parts in nature?"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 361185.0,
      "end_time": 364480.0,
      "text": "I wasn&#39;t raised in a religious Jewish home,"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 364480.0,
      "end_time": 365660.0,
      "text": "but when I was young,"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 365660.0,
      "end_time": 369081.0,
      "text": "my grandmother used to tell me stories from the Hebrew Bible,"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 369081.0,
      "end_time": 373110.0,
      "text": "and one of them stuck with me and came to define much of what I care about."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 373110.0,
      "end_time": 375142.0,
      "text": "As she recounts:"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 375142.0,
      "end_time": 378109.0,
      "text": "&quot;On the third day of Creation, God commands the Earth"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 378109.0,
      "end_time": 380649.0,
      "text": "to grow a fruit-bearing fruit tree.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 380649.0,
      "end_time": 383900.0,
      "text": "For this first fruit tree, there was to be no differentiation"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 383900.0,
      "end_time": 388294.0,
      "text": "between trunk, branches, leaves and fruit."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 388294.0,
      "end_time": 392229.0,
      "text": "The whole tree was a fruit."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 392229.0,
      "end_time": 398337.0,
      "text": "Instead, the land grew trees that have bark and stems and flowers."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 398337.0,
      "end_time": 402514.0,
      "text": "The land created a world made of parts."
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 402514.0,
      "end_time": 404396.0,
      "text": "I often ask myself,"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 404396.0,
      "end_time": 409412.0,
      "text": "&quot;What would design be like if objects were made of a single part?"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 409412.0,
      "end_time": 414999.0,
      "text": "Would we return to a better state of creation?&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 414999.0,
      "end_time": 416978.0,
      "text": "So we looked for that biblical material,"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 416978.0,
      "end_time": 423494.0,
      "text": "that fruit-bearing fruit tree kind of material, and we found it."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 423494.0,
      "end_time": 427274.0,
      "text": "The second-most abundant biopolymer on the planet is called chitin,"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 427274.0,
      "end_time": 430999.0,
      "text": "and some 100 million tons of it are produced every year"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 430999.0,
      "end_time": 435259.0,
      "text": "by organisms such as shrimps, crabs, scorpions and butterflies."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 435259.0,
      "end_time": 437999.0,
      "text": "We thought if we could tune its properties,"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 437999.0,
      "end_time": 440651.0,
      "text": "we could generate structures that are multifunctional"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 440651.0,
      "end_time": 442235.0,
      "text": "out of a single part."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 442235.0,
      "end_time": 444999.0,
      "text": "So that&#39;s what we did."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 444999.0,
      "end_time": 447016.0,
      "text": "We called Legal Seafood --"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 447016.0,
      "end_time": 448076.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 448076.0,
      "end_time": 450957.0,
      "text": "we ordered a bunch of shrimp shells,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 450957.0,
      "end_time": 454583.0,
      "text": "we grinded them and we produced chitosan paste."
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 454583.0,
      "end_time": 456571.0,
      "text": "By varying chemical concentrations,"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 456571.0,
      "end_time": 459889.0,
      "text": "we were able to achieve a wide array of properties --"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 459889.0,
      "end_time": 461690.0,
      "text": "from dark, stiff and opaque,"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 461690.0,
      "end_time": 464689.0,
      "text": "to light, soft and transparent."
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 464689.0,
      "end_time": 467653.0,
      "text": "In order to print the structures in large scale,"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 467653.0,
      "end_time": 472390.0,
      "text": "we built a robotically controlled extrusion system with multiple nozzles."
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 472390.0,
      "end_time": 475572.0,
      "text": "The robot would vary material properties on the fly"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 475572.0,
      "end_time": 480699.0,
      "text": "and create these 12-foot-long structures made of a single material,"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 480699.0,
      "end_time": 483465.0,
      "text": "100 percent recyclable."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 483465.0,
      "end_time": 486163.0,
      "text": "When the parts are ready, they&#39;re left to dry"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 486163.0,
      "end_time": 490313.0,
      "text": "and find a form naturally upon contact with air."
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 490313.0,
      "end_time": 495999.0,
      "text": "So why are we still designing with plastics?"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 495999.0,
      "end_time": 499486.0,
      "text": "The air bubbles that were a byproduct of the printing process"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 499486.0,
      "end_time": 502386.0,
      "text": "were used to contain photosynthetic microorganisms"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 502386.0,
      "end_time": 505283.0,
      "text": "that first appeared on our planet 3.5 billion year ago,"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 505283.0,
      "end_time": 507999.0,
      "text": "as we learned yesterday."
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 507999.0,
      "end_time": 510610.0,
      "text": "Together with our collaborators at Harvard and MIT,"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 510610.0,
      "end_time": 513387.0,
      "text": "we embedded bacteria that were genetically engineered"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 513386.99999999994,
      "end_time": 516552.99999999994,
      "text": "to rapidly capture carbon from the atmosphere"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 516553.0,
      "end_time": 519449.0,
      "text": "and convert it into sugar."
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 519448.99999999994,
      "end_time": 521259.99999999994,
      "text": "For the first time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 521260.0,
      "end_time": 525250.0,
      "text": "we were able to generate structures that would seamlessly transition"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 525250.0,
      "end_time": 528608.0,
      "text": "from beam to mesh,"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 528608.0,
      "end_time": 532019.0,
      "text": "and if scaled even larger, to windows."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 532019.0,
      "end_time": 534626.0,
      "text": "A fruit-bearing fruit tree."
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 534626.0,
      "end_time": 537336.0,
      "text": "Working with an ancient material,"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 537336.0,
      "end_time": 539999.0,
      "text": "one of the first lifeforms on the planet,"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 539999.0,
      "end_time": 543999.0,
      "text": "plenty of water and a little bit of synthetic biology,"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 543999.0,
      "end_time": 547530.0,
      "text": "we were able to transform a structure made of shrimp shells"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 547530.0,
      "end_time": 551724.0,
      "text": "into an architecture that behaves like a tree."
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 551724.0,
      "end_time": 554049.0,
      "text": "And here&#39;s the best part:"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 554049.0,
      "end_time": 556020.0,
      "text": "for objects designed to biodegrade,"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 556020.0,
      "end_time": 559740.0,
      "text": "put them in the sea, and they will nourish marine life;"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 559740.0,
      "end_time": 564415.0,
      "text": "place them in soil, and they will help grow a tree."
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 564415.0,
      "end_time": 568456.0,
      "text": "The setting for our next exploration using the same design principles"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 568456.0,
      "end_time": 570693.0,
      "text": "was the solar system."
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 570693.0,
      "end_time": 574999.0,
      "text": "We looked for the possibility of creating life-sustaining clothing"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 574999.0,
      "end_time": 578707.0,
      "text": "for interplanetary voyages."
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 578707.0,
      "end_time": 583769.0,
      "text": "To do that, we needed to contain bacteria and be able to control their flow."
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 583769.0,
      "end_time": 588353.0,
      "text": "So like the periodic table, we came up with our own table of the elements:"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 588353.0,
      "end_time": 591766.0,
      "text": "new lifeforms that were computationally grown,"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 591766.0,
      "end_time": 593831.0,
      "text": "additively manufactured"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 593831.0,
      "end_time": 598096.0,
      "text": "and biologically augmented."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 598096.0,
      "end_time": 601645.0,
      "text": "I like to think of synthetic biology as liquid alchemy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 601645.0,
      "end_time": 604408.0,
      "text": "only instead of transmuting precious metals,"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 604408.0,
      "end_time": 608171.0,
      "text": "you&#39;re synthesizing new biological functionality inside very small channels."
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 608171.0,
      "end_time": 611067.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s called microfluidics."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 611067.0,
      "end_time": 615266.0,
      "text": "We 3D-printed our own channels in order to control the flow"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 615266.0,
      "end_time": 619432.0,
      "text": "of these liquid bacterial cultures."
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 619432.0,
      "end_time": 623457.0,
      "text": "In our first piece of clothing, we combined two microorganisms."
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 623457.0,
      "end_time": 625392.0,
      "text": "The first is cyanobacteria."
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 625392.0,
      "end_time": 628392.0,
      "text": "It lives in our oceans and in freshwater ponds."
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 628392.0,
      "end_time": 632862.0,
      "text": "And the second, E. coli, the bacterium that inhabits the human gut."
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 632862.0,
      "end_time": 636459.0,
      "text": "One converts light into sugar, the other consumes that sugar"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 636459.0,
      "end_time": 639832.0,
      "text": "and produces biofuels useful for the built environment."
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 639832.0,
      "end_time": 644343.0,
      "text": "Now, these two microorganisms never interact in nature."
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 644343.0,
      "end_time": 646225.0,
      "text": "In fact, they never met each other."
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 646225.0,
      "end_time": 649428.0,
      "text": "They&#39;ve been here, engineered for the first time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 649428.0,
      "end_time": 653340.0,
      "text": "to have a relationship inside a piece of clothing."
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 653340.0,
      "end_time": 656999.0,
      "text": "Think of it as evolution not by natural selection,"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 656999.0,
      "end_time": 659515.0,
      "text": "but evolution by design."
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 659515.0,
      "end_time": 661738.0,
      "text": "In order to contain these relationships,"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 661738.0,
      "end_time": 665867.0,
      "text": "we&#39;ve created a single channel that resembles the digestive tract,"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 665867.0,
      "end_time": 670822.0,
      "text": "that will help flow these bacteria and alter their function along the way."
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 670822.0,
      "end_time": 674475.0,
      "text": "We then started growing these channels on the human body,"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 674475.0,
      "end_time": 677828.0,
      "text": "varying material properties according to the desired functionality."
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 677828.0,
      "end_time": 683101.0,
      "text": "Where we wanted more photosynthesis, we would design more transparent channels."
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 683101.0,
      "end_time": 688229.0,
      "text": "This wearable digestive system, when it&#39;s stretched end to end,"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 688229.0,
      "end_time": 690317.0,
      "text": "spans 60 meters."
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 690317.0,
      "end_time": 692999.0,
      "text": "This is half the length of a football field,"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 692999.0,
      "end_time": 697612.0,
      "text": "and 10 times as long as our small intestines."
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 697612.0,
      "end_time": 700344.0,
      "text": "And here it is for the first time unveiled at TED --"
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 700344.0,
      "end_time": 702471.0,
      "text": "our first photosynthetic wearable,"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 702471.0,
      "end_time": 706694.0,
      "text": "liquid channels glowing with life inside a wearable clothing."
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 706694.0,
      "end_time": 707846.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 707846.0,
      "end_time": 711871.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 711871.0,
      "end_time": 715871.0,
      "text": "Mary Shelley said, &quot;We are unfashioned creatures, but only half made up.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 715871.0,
      "end_time": 719776.0,
      "text": "What if design could provide that other half?"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 719776.0,
      "end_time": 726035.0,
      "text": "What if we could create structures that would augment living matter?"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 726035.0,
      "end_time": 729492.0,
      "text": "What if we could create personal microbiomes"
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 729492.0,
      "end_time": 733391.0,
      "text": "that would scan our skins, repair damaged tissue"
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 733391.0,
      "end_time": 736062.0,
      "text": "and sustain our bodies?"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 736062.0,
      "end_time": 738999.0,
      "text": "Think of this as a form of edited biology."
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 738999.0,
      "end_time": 742999.0,
      "text": "This entire collection, Wanderers, that was named after planets,"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 742999.0,
      "end_time": 745681.0,
      "text": "was not to me really about fashion per se,"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 745681.0,
      "end_time": 749064.0,
      "text": "but it provided an opportunity to speculate about the future"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 749064.0,
      "end_time": 751710.0,
      "text": "of our race on our planet and beyond,"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 751710.0,
      "end_time": 755465.0,
      "text": "to combine scientific insight with lots of mystery"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 755465.0,
      "end_time": 758810.0,
      "text": "and to move away from the age of the machine"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 758810.0,
      "end_time": 762310.0,
      "text": "to a new age of symbiosis between our bodies,"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 762310.0,
      "end_time": 764773.0,
      "text": "the microorganisms that we inhabit,"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 764773.0,
      "end_time": 766725.0,
      "text": "our products and even our buildings."
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 766725.0,
      "end_time": 769591.0,
      "text": "I call this material ecology."
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 769591.0,
      "end_time": 774999.0,
      "text": "To do this, we always need to return back to nature."
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 774999.0,
      "end_time": 779759.0,
      "text": "By now, you know that a 3D printer prints material in layers."
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 779759.0,
      "end_time": 782182.0,
      "text": "You also know that nature doesn&#39;t."
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 782182.0,
      "end_time": 786102.0,
      "text": "It grows. It adds with sophistication."
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 786102.0,
      "end_time": 788690.0,
      "text": "This silkworm cocoon, for example,"
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 788690.0,
      "end_time": 792034.0,
      "text": "creates a highly sophisticated architecture,"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 792034.0,
      "end_time": 794859.0,
      "text": "a home inside which to metamorphisize."
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 794859.0,
      "end_time": 800535.0,
      "text": "No additive manufacturing today gets even close to this level of sophistication."
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 800535.0,
      "end_time": 803631.0,
      "text": "It does so by combining not two materials,"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 803631.0,
      "end_time": 807487.0,
      "text": "but two proteins in different concentrations."
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 807487.0,
      "end_time": 811507.0,
      "text": "One acts as the structure, the other is the glue, or the matrix,"
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 811507.0,
      "end_time": 813952.0,
      "text": "holding those fibers together."
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 813952.0,
      "end_time": 816717.0,
      "text": "And this happens across scales."
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 816717.0,
      "end_time": 819473.0,
      "text": "The silkworm first attaches itself to the environment --"
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 819473.0,
      "end_time": 821513.0,
      "text": "it creates a tensile structure --"
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 821513.0,
      "end_time": 824999.0,
      "text": "and it then starts spinning a compressive cocoon."
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 824999.0,
      "end_time": 828554.0,
      "text": "Tension and compression, the two forces of life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 828554.0,
      "end_time": 833337.0,
      "text": "manifested in a single material."
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 833337.0,
      "end_time": 836572.0,
      "text": "In order to better understand how this complex process works,"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 836572.0,
      "end_time": 838783.0,
      "text": "we glued a tiny earth magnet"
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 838783.0,
      "end_time": 841806.0,
      "text": "to the head of a silkworm, to the spinneret."
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 841806.0,
      "end_time": 844778.0,
      "text": "We placed it inside a box with magnetic sensors,"
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 844778.0,
      "end_time": 847889.0,
      "text": "and that allowed us to create this 3-dimensional point cloud"
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 847889.0,
      "end_time": 853736.0,
      "text": "and visualize the complex architecture of the silkworm cocoon."
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 853736.0,
      "end_time": 857414.0,
      "text": "However, when we placed the silkworm on a flat patch,"
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 857414.0,
      "end_time": 859176.0,
      "text": "not inside a box,"
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 859176.0,
      "end_time": 862391.0,
      "text": "we realized it would spin a flat cocoon"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 862391.0,
      "end_time": 865781.0,
      "text": "and it would still healthily metamorphisize."
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 865781.0,
      "end_time": 869790.0,
      "text": "So we started designing different environments, different scaffolds,"
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 869790.0,
      "end_time": 872549.0,
      "text": "and we discovered that the shape, the composition,"
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 872549.0,
      "end_time": 876866.0,
      "text": "the structure of the cocoon, was directly informed by the environment."
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 876866.0,
      "end_time": 881243.0,
      "text": "Silkworms are often boiled to death inside their cocoons,"
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 881243.0,
      "end_time": 884933.0,
      "text": "their silk unraveled and used in the textile industry."
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 884933.0,
      "end_time": 891416.0,
      "text": "We realized that designing these templates allowed us to give shape to raw silk"
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 891416.0,
      "end_time": 894950.0,
      "text": "without boiling a single cocoon."
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 894950.0,
      "end_time": 898217.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 898217.0,
      "end_time": 900963.0,
      "text": "They would healthily metamorphisize,"
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 900963.0,
      "end_time": 903517.0,
      "text": "and we would be able to create these things."
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 903517.0,
      "end_time": 907170.0,
      "text": "So we scaled this process up to architectural scale."
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 907170.0,
      "end_time": 910325.0,
      "text": "We had a robot spin the template out of silk,"
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 910325.0,
      "end_time": 912489.0,
      "text": "and we placed it on our site."
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 912489.0,
      "end_time": 917397.0,
      "text": "We knew silkworms migrated toward darker and colder areas,"
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 917397.0,
      "end_time": 920741.0,
      "text": "so we used a sun path diagram to reveal the distribution"
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 920741.0,
      "end_time": 923692.0,
      "text": "of light and heat on our structure."
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 923692.0,
      "end_time": 926226.0,
      "text": "We then created holes, or apertures,"
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 926226.0,
      "end_time": 929999.0,
      "text": "that would lock in the rays of light and heat,"
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 929999.0,
      "end_time": 934777.0,
      "text": "distributing those silkworms on the structure."
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 934777.0,
      "end_time": 937174.0,
      "text": "We were ready to receive the caterpillars."
    },
    {
      "index": 271,
      "start_time": 937174.0,
      "end_time": 942031.0,
      "text": "We ordered 6,500 silkworms from an online silk farm."
    },
    {
      "index": 272,
      "start_time": 942031.0,
      "end_time": 945983.0,
      "text": "And after four weeks of feeding, they were ready to spin with us."
    },
    {
      "index": 273,
      "start_time": 945983.0,
      "end_time": 949539.0,
      "text": "We placed them carefully at the bottom rim of the scaffold,"
    },
    {
      "index": 274,
      "start_time": 949539.0,
      "end_time": 953999.0,
      "text": "and as they spin they pupate, they mate, they lay eggs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 275,
      "start_time": 953999.0,
      "end_time": 960300.0,
      "text": "and life begins all over again -- just like us but much, much shorter."
    },
    {
      "index": 276,
      "start_time": 960300.0,
      "end_time": 965069.0,
      "text": "Bucky Fuller said that tension is the great integrity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 277,
      "start_time": 965069.0,
      "end_time": 966716.0,
      "text": "and he was right."
    },
    {
      "index": 278,
      "start_time": 966716.0,
      "end_time": 970462.0,
      "text": "As they spin biological silk over robotically spun silk,"
    },
    {
      "index": 279,
      "start_time": 970462.0,
      "end_time": 973150.0,
      "text": "they give this entire pavilion its integrity."
    },
    {
      "index": 280,
      "start_time": 973150.0,
      "end_time": 975024.0,
      "text": "And over two to three weeks,"
    },
    {
      "index": 281,
      "start_time": 975024.0,
      "end_time": 979703.0,
      "text": "6,500 silkworms spin 6,500 kilometers."
    },
    {
      "index": 282,
      "start_time": 979703.0,
      "end_time": 984837.0,
      "text": "In a curious symmetry, this is also the length of the Silk Road."
    },
    {
      "index": 283,
      "start_time": 984837.0,
      "end_time": 988716.0,
      "text": "The moths, after they hatch, produce 1.5 million eggs."
    },
    {
      "index": 284,
      "start_time": 988716.0,
      "end_time": 993639.0,
      "text": "This could be used for 250 additional pavilions for the future."
    },
    {
      "index": 285,
      "start_time": 993639.0,
      "end_time": 996728.0,
      "text": "So here they are, the two worldviews."
    },
    {
      "index": 286,
      "start_time": 996728.0,
      "end_time": 1000519.0,
      "text": "One spins silk out of a robotic arm,"
    },
    {
      "index": 287,
      "start_time": 1000520.0,
      "end_time": 1004183.0,
      "text": "the other fills in the gaps."
    },
    {
      "index": 288,
      "start_time": 1004180.0,
      "end_time": 1007985.0,
      "text": "If the final frontier of design is to breathe life into the products"
    },
    {
      "index": 289,
      "start_time": 1007990.0,
      "end_time": 1009808.0,
      "text": "and the buildings around us,"
    },
    {
      "index": 290,
      "start_time": 1009800.0,
      "end_time": 1011994.0,
      "text": "to form a two-material ecology,"
    },
    {
      "index": 291,
      "start_time": 1012000.0,
      "end_time": 1015628.0,
      "text": "then designers must unite these two worldviews."
    },
    {
      "index": 292,
      "start_time": 1015630.0,
      "end_time": 1020124.0,
      "text": "Which brings us back, of course, to the beginning."
    },
    {
      "index": 293,
      "start_time": 1020120.0,
      "end_time": 1023747.0,
      "text": "Here&#39;s to a new age of design, a new age of creation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 294,
      "start_time": 1023750.0,
      "end_time": 1027122.0,
      "text": "that takes us from a nature-inspired design"
    },
    {
      "index": 295,
      "start_time": 1027119.9999999999,
      "end_time": 1029998.9999999999,
      "text": "to a design-inspired nature,"
    },
    {
      "index": 296,
      "start_time": 1030000.0,
      "end_time": 1034000.0,
      "text": "and that demands of us for the first time"
    },
    {
      "index": 297,
      "start_time": 1034000.0,
      "end_time": 1038794.0,
      "text": "that we mother nature."
    },
    {
      "index": 298,
      "start_time": 1038790.0,
      "end_time": 1039848.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 299,
      "start_time": 1039849.9999999999,
      "end_time": 1046869.9999999999,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 300,
      "start_time": 1046869.9999999999,
      "end_time": 1048998.0,
      "text": "Thank you very much. Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 301,
      "start_time": 1049000.0,
      "end_time": 1059000.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}